<h2>You Don't Need an Expensive Setup</h2>
<p>Most earning platforms work on any device — your phone, an old laptop, whatever. But if you want a dedicated gaming and earning setup that's actually enjoyable to use, $500 gets you surprisingly far in 2026.</p>
<p>Here's how to spend that budget wisely.</p>

<h2>Option A: Mobile-First Setup ($50-150)</h2>
<p>If you're mainly doing <a href="/reviews/freecash">FreeCash</a> gaming offers and surveys, a phone is all you need. Most offers are mobile-first anyway.</p>

<h3>What You Need</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>A decent phone</strong> — anything from the last 3-4 years works. If buying new, a Samsung Galaxy A25 (~$150) or Pixel 7a (~$200) handles everything</li>
  <li><strong>A phone stand</strong> — $10. Sounds trivial but holding your phone for hours gets old</li>
  <li><strong>Earbuds</strong> — any $20-30 pair. Needed for PlaytestCloud tests where you speak aloud</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Total: $50-200</strong> depending on whether you need a new phone.</p>

<h2>Option B: Laptop + Phone Combo ($300-500)</h2>
<p>For multitasking — surveys on the laptop while gaming offers run on your phone. This is the setup that maximizes your $/hour.</p>

<h3>The Build</h3>
<table class="info-table">
  <tr><td>Laptop</td><td>Refurbished ThinkPad or Dell Latitude — $150-250 on Amazon Renewed</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Phone</td><td>Your current phone (or Samsung A25 at $150)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Phone Stand</td><td>Adjustable desk mount — $12</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Mouse</td><td>Logitech G203 — $25 (great budget gaming mouse)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Headset</td><td>HyperX Cloud Stinger 2 — $30 (good mic for PlaytestCloud)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Mousepad</td><td>Large desk pad — $12</td></tr>
</table>

<p><strong>Total: $380-480</strong></p>

<h3>Why a ThinkPad?</h3>
<p>Refurbished ThinkPads are the best value in computing. A 3-year-old ThinkPad T14 with 16GB RAM handles surveys, browsing, and even some PC gaming offers without breaking a sweat. They're built like tanks and have great keyboards. Don't buy a new budget Chromebook — a refurbished business laptop gives you way more for the money.</p>

<h2>Option C: Budget Desktop Gaming ($500)</h2>
<p>If you want to game for real (and earn on the side), $500 builds a capable PC:</p>

<table class="info-table">
  <tr><td>CPU</td><td>AMD Ryzen 5 5600 — $100</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GPU</td><td>RX 6600 or used RTX 3060 — $150-180</td></tr>
  <tr><td>RAM</td><td>16GB DDR4 — $35</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Storage</td><td>500GB NVMe SSD — $35</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Case + PSU</td><td>Budget combo — $70</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Motherboard</td><td>B550M — $60</td></tr>
</table>

<p><strong>Total: ~$470</strong> (add a $30 headset if needed)</p>

<p>This handles 1080p gaming at 60+ FPS in most titles, plus all your earning platform tasks. Buy parts on sale and you can shave another $50 off.</p>

<h2>Gear That Actually Matters for Earning</h2>
<p>If you're focused on maximizing earning potential, spend your money in this order:</p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>A reliable phone</strong> — most offers are mobile-first</li>
  <li><strong>A decent headset with mic</strong> — required for PlaytestCloud, useful for everything</li>
  <li><strong>A second screen (phone or tablet)</strong> — multitask between platforms</li>
  <li><strong>A comfortable chair</strong> — you'll be sitting for hours; don't destroy your back</li>
  <li><strong>Fast internet</strong> — downloads, streaming, and app installs go faster</li>
</ol>

<h2>What NOT to Buy</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>RGB everything</strong> — looks cool, does nothing for your earnings</li>
  <li><strong>$200+ headsets</strong> — a $30 HyperX sounds great for this purpose</li>
  <li><strong>"Gaming" chairs</strong> — a used Herman Miller Aeron ($300 used) is better for your back than any $400 gaming chair. Or just get a decent office chair for $100</li>
  <li><strong>4K monitors</strong> — 1080p is fine for earning platforms and most gaming</li>
</ul>

<h2>Bottom Line</h2>
<p>You can start earning with just your phone — no investment needed. But if you want a comfortable, efficient setup for long-term earning, $300-500 gets you everything you need. Start with Option A, use your earnings to upgrade to Option B or C over time.</p>

